Phase 5b / L-discipline-3 — Bool#rec direct-emission gate.

L-16 closed the path where scNormalize unfolded iteDep/ite to bare
Bool#rec. This test pins the residual path: a hand-written term
(via parse_core) that emits Bool#rec directly. SAW must refuse,
not silently swap branches at every if/then/else translation.

Pairs with the L-16 smoketest "Bool#rec doesn't surface bare in
translated output" — the smoketest pins the negative property
(no Bool#rec leaks through normal emission); this intTest pins
the positive guard (an explicit Bool#rec is rejected by the
RejectedPrimitive path).
